Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.81,0:02:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.65,0:02:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they kill the priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It defies belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.87,0:02:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This cannot be allowed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.30,0:02:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you not tell Tokiomi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.89,0:02:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.60,0:02:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How I pity your father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He died believing his son to be a man of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.10,0:02:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.85,0:02:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might that perhaps have been his salvation?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.57,0:02:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does your father's death leave you indifferent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might look a little sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... It bothers me to no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that because you were unable to kill him yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.18,0:03:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisviel, how are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears I've made you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, as long as you truly are all right, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.86,0:03:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.37,0:03:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This presence is Maiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.87,0:03:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.63,0:03:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka Tokiomi requests an alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An alliance? Now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka is surely uneasy at the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of dealing with Rider and Berserker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.35,0:04:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he invited us to meet, assuming we are the most likely to favor a collaboration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that he believes we are the weakest of the lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka said he wishes to meet tonight, at the Fuyuki City church.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.24,0:04:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the start, Tohsaka Tokiomi has made elaborate preparations for this Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, it's also likely that he controlled Assassin's Master, Kotomine Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Tohsaka holds some power over Kotomine Kirei,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.34,0:04:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then we cannot ignore this offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:04:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotomine Kirei...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.85,0:04:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep this in mind, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.27,0:05:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there is anyone who can defeat Kiritsugu to win the Holy Grail War,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is Kotomine Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.53,0:05:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.57,0:05:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father would like to speak with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.38,0:06:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you grow up, try to keep the Church in your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond that, I leave the rest up to your judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.97,0:06:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.10,0:06:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, the Holy Grail will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the responsibility of the Tohsakas to attain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.65,0:06:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Above all,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you wish to be a magus, that is the path you must follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rin. Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.50,0:06:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be going then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what to do now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, allow me to thank you for coming at my behest.{joined like 3 nicolines here so feel free to split}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.66,0:07:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Kotomine Kirei, my student.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While we were once competitors for the Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all that is now in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has lost his Servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.22,0:07:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has yielded his rights as a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Grail War is heading toward its conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.22,0:07:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones remaining are,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.68,0:07:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as anticipated, the Masters of the three houses,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,along with one outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.61,0:07:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, how would you appraise this war?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Grail must not be allowed to fall into outside hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.03,0:07:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We two should at least be able to agree on that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.50,0:08:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any alliance is out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if you wish to discuss the order in which we approach our enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.13,0:08:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we may be able to come to some agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.59,0:08:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can settle things with the Tohsakas after we have defeated the other Masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are prepared to agree to such a proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.47,0:08:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So a temporary, conditional ceasefire?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fair compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.52,0:08:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have two conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.11,0:08:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, that you share any information you have concerning Rider and his Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our second request is to remove\N Kotomine Kirei from the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Would you explain your reasons?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There is bad blood between\N the Einzberns and the Executor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.51,0:08:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the Tohsakas continue to protect him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we will find ourselves unable to trust you regardless of circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does she refer to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.57,0:09:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you like Kiritsugu's present?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more like a horse than a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to suit me better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.70,0:09:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I shall go ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and ensure that the route is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.80,0:09:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us go as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.22,0:09:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Madam..
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead, Maiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.93,0:09:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka will realize something is amiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.61,0:10:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't unexpected...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.03,0:10:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.70,0:10:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, the fact that I've been able to function as a human for this long is a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.34,0:10:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a homunculus created for the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.05,0:10:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.51,0:10:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather Acht gave the vessel an instinct for self-preservation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that it would avoid all danger and\N safeguard the Grail to its completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.85,0:10:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He disguised the vessel, and called it Irisviel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.24,0:10:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.99,0:10:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.28,0:10:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.99,0:10:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.49,0:10:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will return to being as I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't even be able to talk to you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.34,0:10:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Kiritsugu gave me Saber's scabbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.63,0:10:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Avalon..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.13,0:11:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you familiar with what it does?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Halts aging, alongside an infinite healing power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.01,0:11:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I've been told.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.64,0:11:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its effects are what has stopped the shell that is me from collapsing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, when Saber isn't nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.65,0:11:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it does not work as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why tell me this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.57,0:11:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hisau Maiya...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You would never pity me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd accept me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.17,0:11:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.55,0:11:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have always thought of you as a more distant figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.26,0:11:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.93,0:11:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.55,0:11:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even at the cost of my own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisviel,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.93,0:11:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will see you to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.94,0:11:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.52,0:11:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,die for Emiya Kiritsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make his dream a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have preferred to have known
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of your relationship with the Einzberns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must withdraw from the Grail War,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.01,0:12:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Emiya Kiritsugu...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.95,0:12:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will I leave this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}never even knowing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still thinking, even now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.04,0:12:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you truly be so slow, Kirei?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:13:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Grail beckons you still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and you still long to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I can remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have spent my life in search of a single thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.48,0:13:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've invested all my time into it. Endured great pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.11,0:13:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But all of that has come to naught.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, I want the answer now,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.86,0:13:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,more than I ever did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that self-examination,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so why do you hesitate?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.37,0:13:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a premonition...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.41,0:13:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That when I've learned all the answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.75,0:13:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall destroy myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely, that was quite an exciting revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.43,0:13:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've learned the location of the Einzberns' hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, Kirei? You honestly amaze me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All this time, were you not planning to continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.70,0:14:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was prepared to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.41,0:14:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, it is as you say, King of Heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know no other way than to keep asking the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.00,0:14:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gift from my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.93,0:14:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,JN424.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Gospel of John.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.52,0:14:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God is spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and those who worship him must worship in spirit and in truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.74,0:14:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Kirei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very serious problem remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.12,0:15:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you choose to participate in the Grail War,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.46,0:15:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka Tokiomi will become your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.29,0:15:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you are standing unprepared
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.84,0:15:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the same room as an enemy Servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.59,0:15:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this not a dire situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.39,0:15:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.31,0:15:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prepared to beg for my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gilgamesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me tell you the truth behind the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.03,0:15:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.40,0:15:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ritual here in Fuyuki is an attempt to open a passage to Akasha
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,through the sacrifice of seven Heroic Spirits' souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.75,0:15:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By killing all seven Servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one may activate the Great Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.88,0:15:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, all seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.59,0:15:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the reason my master has worked so hard
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.97,0:15:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid using his Command Seals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:16:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because when all the battles end, he requires it to force his own Servant to commit suicide.{gotta pull a Lancer there}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the loyalty Tokiomi has shown me was all a lie, you claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put another way, my master is a magus to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may worship a Heroic Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he harbors no illusions about his idols.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.87,0:16:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokiomi...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.79,0:16:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, you have proven your worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.17,0:16:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That boring little man will be able to entertain me at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.42,0:16:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, what will you do, King of Heroes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you remain loyal to my master and ask me my true intent?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, I hardly know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite his disloyalty,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokiomi still supplies me with prana.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.07,0:16:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were I to abandon my Master, it would hinder my ability to remain materialized...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.45,0:16:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.87,0:16:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is one with a Command Seal, but no partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One searching for a Servant unbound by contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.79,0:17:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But is that man worthy of being a Master in the eyes of the King of Heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He will suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is, perhaps, a bit stiff,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.39,0:17:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he has great potential for growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.22,0:17:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may yet prove a fine source of entertainment for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.52,0:17:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting, Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.23,0:17:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to have a word before departing Fuyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.16,0:17:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still proud to have had you as my student.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you will maintain good relations with the Tohsakas, as your father did...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.51,0:17:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.34,0:17:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your words honor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:18:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this Grail War has ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.35,0:18:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like for you to help train Rin, Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.64,0:18:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's simple, but in essence, it's a will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it wise to prepare for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It leaves the Tohsaka family wealth to Rin,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.87,0:18:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and names you as her guardian until she comes of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall do all I can to look after your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.26,0:18:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.13,0:18:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gift from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.26,0:18:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.18,0:18:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Azoth dagger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.48,0:18:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It symbolizes your mastery of the Tohsaka family magics,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.11,0:18:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and marks the end of your apprenticeship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:19:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are far too kind to me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot begin to express my gratitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.12,0:19:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.95,0:19:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is I who must thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotomine Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can prepare for the final battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.09,0:19:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to have kept you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.80,0:19:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you will make it in time for your flight...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.69,0:19:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.36,0:19:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.40,0:19:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.24,0:19:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never bought a ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You never did understand me until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a boring ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.95,0:20:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that idiotic face.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.62,0:20:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did have a dematerialized Servant at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.25,0:20:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was hardly illogical for him to lower his guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've already learned to jest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.92,0:20:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a quick learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.59,0:20:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Kirei?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you feel a little better about not having had the chance to kill your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.89,0:20:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really have no qualms,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.56,0:20:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,King of Heroes, Gilgamesh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.35,0:20:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so long as you continue to amuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.48,0:21:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once things change, Kirei...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.03,0:21:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you ought to question your own resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.37,0:21:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My will creates your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.53,0:21:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and your sword creates my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.87,0:21:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you heed the Grail's call
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and obey my will and reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.21,0:21:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.42,0:21:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your offering will be my flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.25,0:21:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotomine Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My new Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.09,0:21:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.55,0:21:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.64,0:21:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put an end to this farce,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,howsoever you see fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a reward, I shall hand you the Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.27,0:21:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.90,0:21:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,King of Heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.11,0:21:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May you have your fill of amusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.78,0:21:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I find the answer I seek,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall gladly play the fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.87,0:21:54.91,type,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\pos(642,257)}Episode 17 \NThe Eighth Contract
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.95,0:22:00.71,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2}Why is the sky so blue
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:05.67,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2}as if it knows nothing of sadness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.67,0:22:14.72,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2}Each day our ruin advances a step, yet we do not falter
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.72,0:22:21.94,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2\3c&H306DF0&}We are forever reborn, only to fail
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.94,0:22:29.74,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2\3c&H3C77E2&\blur2\fad(100,100)}You touched my soul when I had run from battle
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.74,0:22:34.74,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HDBC68F&\blur2\fad(100,100)}a{\3c&HD7C18D&}n{\3c&HD3BC8C&}d{\3c&HD0B88B&} {\3c&HCDB48B&}t{\3c&HCAB18A&}o{\3c&HC6AB88&}g{\3c&HC2A687&}e{\3c&HBFA186&}t{\3c&HBC9E85&}h{\3c&HB89984&}e{\3c&HB49483&}r{\3c&HB29182&} {\3c&HAE8C81&}w{\3c&HAA8680&}e{\3c&HA6827F&} {\3c&HA37D7E&}w{\3c&H9F787D&}i{\3c&H9D767C&}l{\3c&H9B747C&}l{\3c&H9B737B&} {\3c&H9C737A&}w{\3c&H9E7479&}a{\3c&H9F7479&}l{\3c&HA07578&}k{\3c&HA17578&} {\3c&HA27577&}i{\3c&HA37676&}n{\3c&HA47676&}t{\3c&HA57775&}o{\3c&HA67774&} {\3c&HA77874&}t{\3c&HA97873&}h{\3c&HAA7972&}e{\3c&HAB7971&} {\3c&HAC7971&}f{\3c&HAD7A70&}u{\3c&HAE7A70&}t{\3c&HAF7B6F&}u{\3c&HB07B6E&}r{\3c&HB27C6E&}e
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.74,0:22:40.63,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HDBC68F&\blur2\fad(100,100)}with a strength empty of sin and vice
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.63,0:22:45.63,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HDBC68F&\blur2\fad(100,100)}The sky is all around me, the wind sings in it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.63,0:22:50.64,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\3c&HDBC68F&\blur2\fad(100,100)}Will men one day
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.64,0:22:55.77,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2\3c&HE9E16C&}find the happiness they dreamed of?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.77,0:23:03.15,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2\3c&HDAC33B&}You had faith when you saw the eyes of a child
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.15,0:23:05.65,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2\3c&H5F3B39&}I'm here right next to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:10.70,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)\blur2}{\3c&HC1A7BE&}Making our way past this icy forest
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.70,0:23:22.83,ED2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,1000)\blur2\3c&HB38999&}I pray that the grief of this world will not sway your determination
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.59,0:23:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kerry, what do you want to be when you grow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.51,0:23:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go to that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.72,0:23:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.05,0:23:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Decide the rest for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.89,0:23:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still too early for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.72,0:23:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, you'll have the power to change the world.
